cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL. 

This paper involves the use of deep generative neural networks for decoding and reconstructing images from brain imaging data, specifically fMRI patterns. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of a large-scale bi-directional generative adversarial network, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of a linear mapping between fMRI data and latent vectors, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves the use of class and attribute information in the latent space, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves the assessment of the resulting image reconstructions, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
